Module org.autogui
Package org.autogui.base.type

Class GuiTypeMemberPropertyNotifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.autogui.base.type.GuiTypeMember
      • org.autogui.base.type.GuiTypeMemberProperty
        • org.autogui.base.type.GuiTypeMemberPropertyNotifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GuiTypeElement
    public class GuiTypeMemberPropertyNotifier
extends GuiTypeMemberProperty
    a type information about setter of notifier: basically, it is intended to have only a setter with the GuiNotifierSetter annotation 
       @GuiNotifierSetter public void setNotifier(Runnable r) { ... }
    The name of the setter is intended to be "setTargetNotifier", where Target specifies another name target of the property of the owner type as the target of notifying, or the empty string "" if the target is the object of the type itself.

    GuiNotifierSetter.target() can explicitly set the target name and there are 3 special names, GuiNotifierSetter.TARGET_FROM_NAME (default, and then above Target is used), GuiNotifierSetter.TARGET_SELF and GuiNotifierSetter.TARGET_ROOT.

    Since:
    1.2
